[[File:Virgilius Alekna Berlin 2009.JPG|thumb|Alekna at his eighth World Championships in 2009, Berlin.]]

Alekna was awarded the title of the Athlete of the Year for 2000 by [[Track and Field News]]. He was also awarded the [[Order of the Lithuanian Grand Duke Gediminas]] by the government of Lithuania. He became the [[Lithuanian Sportsman of the Year]] 4 times (2000, 2004, 2005, and 2006). Since 1995 Alekna has served as a bodyguard of the Lithuanian Prime Minister.

He is married to former long jumper Kristina Sablovskyt<U+0117>-Aleknien<U+0117> and has two young sons named Martynas and Mykolas.

At a height of 2.00 m (6 ft 7 in), Alekna has an abnormally long wingspan, measured 2.22m (7 ft 3.5 in), which is useful for discus throwing.  He can make fingerprints on windows of two opposite sides of a bus simultaneously.<ref>[http://www.iaaf.org/news/Kind=2/newsId=14438.html IAAF]</ref>

During the [[2007 World Championships in Athletics|2007 World Championship]] Virgilijus Alekna competed with an injury. Having sustained the injury on 20 August, he competed in the World Championship's qualification on 28 August<ref name=ES> {{lt icon}} Egl<U+0117> <U+0160>ilinskait<U+0117>. [http://www.lrytas.lt/?data=20070829&id=spo29_a1070829&sk_id=99&view=2 Nenugalim<U+0105>j<U+012F> metik<U+0105> <U+012F>veik<U+0117> kojos trauma (Unbeatable thrower was defeat by leg injury)]. Retrieved on 2007-08-29</ref> and, as a result, suffered a defeat, which broke his 37 victories in a row over the past two years.<ref name=ES/>.

